job_history.work_description: Coordinate tracking the Installation Quality Audit reports. Coordinating a process to streamline common processes for the 9 box review for Global Off-Highway Customer Engineering. Coordinate the planning and logistics for conferences and trainings. Support the team's learning and usage of new technology available such as Cummins Connect and Outlook 365. Support new hires and ensuring they receive training, learning about the CCW environment and about basic how to do tasks.

Facilitated modules during CES site OnBoarding. Prepared Training Modules. Created the Right Environment coordinating logistics to ensure participants were in a great learning environment. Process Improvement by participating on a team to update the Aftertreatment 101 module in order to increase employee interaction and to update the use of current technology.
Assisted in the management of a 152 unit apartment community.
Basic classroom instruction and management - Used Project Based Learning (PBL) techniques that helped students see the connection between classroom learning and real world application.
Developed, planned and implemented summer and after school programs for over 200 youth ages 5-18.
